&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits Administration &amp;amp; Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage global benefits operations across the US, Canada, UK, and Ireland, overseeing benefit administration, invoice tracking, and the processing and reconciliation of payments across approximately 20 vendors (including medical, dental, and life insurance)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct monthly audits of benefit plans, identifying discrepancies and driving resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer global pension and retirement schemes (UK, Ireland, US), including system uploads and quarterly fee tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee FSA/HSA funding aligned with payroll cycles, including quarterly employer contributions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer COBRA processes and maintain associated tracking documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Evidence of Insurability (EOI) approvals and send follow-ups for pending submissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HR Systems &amp;amp; Data Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate employee data across Workday and related systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve Qualified Life Event (QLE) benefit changes, including manual FSA/HSA adjustments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process benefits onboarding, employee changes, beneficiary updates, and one-time employee payments (e.g., bonuses, reimbursements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and troubleshoot weekly benefits integration files to ensure data accuracy and integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run and review reports including Terminated with Benefits, Business Process Transactions, and quarterly dependent/beneficiary audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
